1
00:01:07,015 --> 00:01:10,229
[TEMPLE BELL]

2
00:01:10,851 --> 00:01:15,601
Students, I had told you to
write four lines on your mother.

3
00:01:15,835 --> 00:01:18,595
- Have you all written it?
- Yes, teacher.

4
00:01:18,636 --> 00:01:19,577
Very good.

5
00:01:23,175 --> 00:01:25,851
Raju... Did you write it?

6
00:01:27,005 --> 00:01:29,927
I'm asking you, did you write it?
Come here.

7
00:01:35,420 --> 00:01:38,268
You've not written anything.

8
00:01:38,445 --> 00:01:40,531
Do you sleep in the classroom?

9
00:01:40,714 --> 00:01:42,219
Answer me?

10
00:01:43,845 --> 00:01:47,085
You won't speak like this.
This stick will make you speak up.

11
00:01:47,195 --> 00:01:48,357
Show me your hand.

12
00:01:48,382 --> 00:01:51,782
Tell me. Tell me.

13
00:01:52,774 --> 00:01:56,179
Tell me. Tell me.

14
00:01:56,522 --> 00:01:58,252
Teacher, don't beat him.

15
00:01:58,308 --> 00:02:01,412
How can he write about his mother?
He has no mother.

16
00:04:04,505 --> 00:04:06,623
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

17
00:04:07,403 --> 00:04:09,043
- Hello.
- Call from Delhi.

18
00:04:09,313 --> 00:04:12,268
Call from Delhi. Hang on.
Sir, your call from Delhi.

19
00:04:12,804 --> 00:04:13,833
- Hello.
- Prem.

20
00:04:13,913 --> 00:04:14,889
Yes, Prem here.

21
00:04:14,930 --> 00:04:16,372
- Shrivastav here.
- Who? Shrivastav?

22
00:04:16,435 --> 00:04:18,041
- Uncle Ramu.
- Yes, dear?

23
00:04:18,361 --> 00:04:21,401
- Who is father talking to?
- To someone in Delhi.

24
00:04:21,450 --> 00:04:23,367
Delhi? Delhi is so far away.

25
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:25,589
Forget Delhi, these days.

26
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:28,128
You can even talk to somebody in the sky.

27
00:04:28,169 --> 00:04:29,891
- Even above the clouds?
- Yes.

28
00:04:31,547 --> 00:04:33,377
Don't worry. Your work will be done.

29
00:04:35,137 --> 00:04:37,684
Come on, Raju. Freshen up.
We'll have our meals.

30
00:04:44,639 --> 00:04:45,576
[BELL CHIMES]

31
00:04:46,368 --> 00:04:47,366
[CRICKET CHIRPING]

32
00:04:49,281 --> 00:04:50,184
[CRICKET CHIRPING]

33
00:04:53,257 --> 00:04:54,123
[BELL CHIMES]

34
00:04:57,878 --> 00:04:58,972
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

35
00:05:00,292 --> 00:05:01,972
Hello. Telephone exchange.

36
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:05,090
- I want God's number.
- What? What number?

37
00:05:05,253 --> 00:05:08,373
God's number. I want to talk to my mother.

38
00:05:08,505 --> 00:05:10,261
Is your mother with God?

39
00:05:10,388 --> 00:05:13,908
Yes. She died when I was born.

40
00:05:14,136 --> 00:05:16,086
Tell her it's her Raju's call.

41
00:05:16,127 --> 00:05:17,030
Hang on.

42
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:18,291
- Neeta.
- Yes?

43
00:05:18,394 --> 00:05:20,982
It's a boy. He wants God's number.

44
00:05:21,135 --> 00:05:22,775
He wants to talk to his mother.

45
00:05:22,982 --> 00:05:25,463
Talk to him. It'll make him feel better.

46
00:05:25,808 --> 00:05:27,482
Get lost. Don't bore me.

47
00:05:27,523 --> 00:05:28,952
Please. For my sake.

48
00:05:29,155 --> 00:05:31,429
What's the harm in talking
to him for two minutes?

49
00:05:32,983 --> 00:05:33,847
Fine. Give.

50
00:05:34,778 --> 00:05:36,207
Dear, talk to your mother.

51
00:05:39,724 --> 00:05:41,589
- Hello.
- Mother.

52
00:05:43,941 --> 00:05:47,097
Mother, Raju here. Your Raju.

53
00:05:47,154 --> 00:05:51,074
I know, son. Can't I recognise my Raju?

54
00:05:51,230 --> 00:05:53,910
Mother, you've recognised me. How are you?

55
00:05:54,637 --> 00:05:57,757
I... I'm fine.

56
00:05:58,029 --> 00:06:00,157
I miss you a lot.

57
00:06:00,419 --> 00:06:04,499
Take leave from God and come to me.
Please.

58
00:06:05,082 --> 00:06:07,962
Dear, I can't come. I'm helpless.

59
00:06:08,073 --> 00:06:11,246
Why can't you come? Don't you love me?

60
00:06:12,482 --> 00:06:15,708
I love you a lot, son.

61
00:06:15,755 --> 00:06:17,235
Then why can't you come?

62
00:06:17,363 --> 00:06:20,603
Have I erred, mother? I apologise.

63
00:06:20,817 --> 00:06:24,177
Now I will neither err nor trouble you.

64
00:06:24,302 --> 00:06:26,382
- But Raju, son.
- Don't refuse.

65
00:06:26,707 --> 00:06:30,307
I want to see you. I want to talk to you.

66
00:06:30,761 --> 00:06:33,281
I want to sleep in your lap.

67
00:06:35,884 --> 00:06:38,555
Don't cry, son.

68
00:06:39,204 --> 00:06:41,727
You're my brave son.

69
00:06:41,768 --> 00:06:43,757
Look, Mother. Let me tell you clearly.

70
00:06:44,289 --> 00:06:45,649
Tomorrow is my birthday.

71
00:06:45,965 --> 00:06:49,894
If you won't come, I'll starve to death.

72
00:06:49,935 --> 00:06:52,375
No, son. Don't say that.

73
00:06:52,605 --> 00:06:57,173
Then promise me you'll
come on my birthday. Okay?

74
00:06:58,130 --> 00:06:59,210
I'll come, son.

75
00:06:59,251 --> 00:07:00,862
Don't forget, Mother.

76
00:07:01,022 --> 00:07:03,542
I won't cut the cake until you come.

77
00:07:04,347 --> 00:07:09,508
Your mother will surely
come on your birthday.

78
00:07:10,311 --> 00:07:11,317
Okay, Mother.

79
00:07:20,482 --> 00:07:21,768
Father.

80
00:07:21,932 --> 00:07:23,992
Mother is coming. I just spoke to her.

81
00:07:24,238 --> 00:07:27,057
She said she'll surely
come on my birthday.

82
00:07:32,529 --> 00:07:33,982
Your mother will surely come, son.

83
00:07:35,602 --> 00:07:37,436
She'll surely come on your birthday.

84
00:07:38,405 --> 00:07:39,889
[CHILDREN PLAYING]

85
00:07:42,312 --> 00:07:43,523
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

86
00:07:44,207 --> 00:07:46,791
Raju, quickly cut the cake. I'm famished.

87
00:07:46,832 --> 00:07:48,329
Not now. Only after mother comes.

88
00:07:48,490 --> 00:07:51,689
After your mother comes?
The dead don't come back.

89
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:53,730
My mother will surely come.
She has told me.

90
00:07:53,864 --> 00:07:57,583
He even spoke to his mother.
It must be your mom's ghost.

91
00:07:57,624 --> 00:07:59,749
You call my mother a ghost. I'll kill you.

92
00:08:02,783 --> 00:08:04,849
The power failed.
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

93
00:08:05,723 --> 00:08:08,127
What happened to the electricity?
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

94
00:08:08,168 --> 00:08:09,114
Raju.

95
00:08:16,158 --> 00:08:18,688
'As usual, father lied to me even today.'

96
00:08:18,729 --> 00:08:20,729
'Even today, he didn't bring my mother.'

97
00:08:24,409 --> 00:08:25,569
Laxmi.

98
00:08:58,765 --> 00:08:59,809
Mother.

99
00:09:00,252 --> 00:09:01,289
Son.

100
00:09:45,122 --> 00:09:48,417
"It's a joyous day."

101
00:09:50,744 --> 00:09:54,104
"I got what I wanted."

102
00:09:56,313 --> 00:09:58,953
"It's a joyous day."

103
00:09:59,088 --> 00:10:01,808
"I got what I wanted."

104
00:10:01,849 --> 00:10:07,408
"Today my mother called me son."

105
00:10:07,449 --> 00:10:10,248
"It's a joyous day."

106
00:10:10,289 --> 00:10:12,969
"I got what I wanted."

107
00:10:13,017 --> 00:10:18,617
"Today my mother called me son."

108
00:10:18,692 --> 00:10:23,529
"Mother. My mother."

109
00:10:24,283 --> 00:10:29,330
"Mother. My mother."

110
00:10:29,904 --> 00:10:30,810
- Teacher.
- Yes.

111
00:10:30,851 --> 00:10:32,651
- My mother.
- Is that so?

112
00:10:33,339 --> 00:10:35,049
Aunt, she's my mother.

113
00:10:35,090 --> 00:10:36,136
Yes, son.

114
00:10:57,662 --> 00:11:03,408
"Mother, I've to grow
up under your shelter."

115
00:11:03,449 --> 00:11:08,934
"Holding your finger,
I've to walk with you."

116
00:11:09,479 --> 00:11:14,864
"You're the answer to my prayers."

117
00:11:15,148 --> 00:11:20,256
"You're my God."

118
00:11:20,614 --> 00:11:26,208
"You dwell in each temple and idol."

119
00:11:26,249 --> 00:11:28,942
"It's a joyous day."

120
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:31,778
"I got what I wanted."

121
00:11:31,819 --> 00:11:37,459
"Today my mother called me son."

122
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:56,218
Do you see what I'm seeing, Mainawati?

123
00:11:56,259 --> 00:11:58,019
Yes, Tota.

124
00:11:58,068 --> 00:11:59,979
My name is Totaram, not Tota.

125
00:12:00,020 --> 00:12:02,580
Have your medicine on time.
Don't forget it.

126
00:12:02,743 --> 00:12:05,553
- Sister. My dear sister.
- Brother.

127
00:12:05,594 --> 00:12:08,489
My dear sister. Why did you leave us?

128
00:12:08,530 --> 00:12:12,499
I swear. After getting
married, I've become lonely.

129
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:14,039
- Really, sister. What do I tell you?
- Brother.

130
00:12:14,092 --> 00:12:17,212
He is shedding tears like
a municipal drainage.

131
00:12:17,253 --> 00:12:19,427
Not municipal drainage. Water pipe.

132
00:12:19,468 --> 00:12:20,519
It's one and the same thing.

133
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:23,757
Brother-in-law. Now we won't leave you.

134
00:12:24,795 --> 00:12:25,980
No. Don't cry, Totaram.

135
00:12:26,303 --> 00:12:28,783
- If you want, you can stay with us.
- Really?

136
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:32,207
Laxmi, take him inside.
I'll meet the collector. -Okay.

137
00:12:32,255 --> 00:12:36,375
Brother-in-law is great.

138
00:12:38,751 --> 00:12:41,885
Brother-in-law seems to be
an emotional guy, sister.

139
00:12:41,926 --> 00:12:44,245
Have you got the bungalow,
land and the wealth...

140
00:12:44,286 --> 00:12:45,935
...transferred in your name?

141
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:53,551
Brother, don't worry.

142
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:56,728
Very soon everything will be ours.

143
00:12:56,769 --> 00:12:57,432
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

144
00:12:57,473 --> 00:13:01,709
Sister, we're ruined. We're doomed.

145
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:05,002
- Do you see this Will?
- What is written in this Will?

146
00:13:05,043 --> 00:13:08,003
This will is going to ruin my sister.

147
00:13:08,237 --> 00:13:11,931
I got my sister married to widower Prem.

148
00:13:11,992 --> 00:13:13,952
...to seize his wealth.

149
00:13:14,166 --> 00:13:17,566
But things are different.
Prem is worthless.

150
00:13:17,607 --> 00:13:21,031
She's just the trustee.
She has no right on the wealth.

151
00:13:21,056 --> 00:13:21,676
[COW MOO]

152
00:13:21,717 --> 00:13:23,562
Raju's mother was a cunning woman.

153
00:13:23,787 --> 00:13:26,469
Before dying she bequeathed
everything to Raju.

154
00:13:26,494 --> 00:13:28,234
Oh, my God. It's terrible.

155
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:30,943
Not terrible. It's horrible.

156
00:13:30,968 --> 00:13:33,226
That witch has also willed...

157
00:13:33,247 --> 00:13:35,241
...that until Raju doesn't get married...

158
00:13:35,282 --> 00:13:38,246
...and his wife's doesn't
give her consent...

159
00:13:38,278 --> 00:13:41,689
...Raju can't transfer
the wealth to anyone else.

160
00:13:41,730 --> 00:13:45,610
It's fine by us,
but what about sister's to-be born child?

161
00:13:45,855 --> 00:13:48,032
- He should get his right.
- Yes.

162
00:13:50,438 --> 00:13:53,370
My child will surely get his right.

163
00:13:53,411 --> 00:13:55,029
[BIRD CHIRPING] - Just watch, brother.

164
00:13:55,496 --> 00:13:57,444
I'll cast such a spell on Raju...

165
00:13:58,182 --> 00:14:03,080
...he'll chant "mother" day and night.

166
00:14:03,947 --> 00:14:05,412
He'll live for his mother.

167
00:14:06,317 --> 00:14:08,817
He'll die for his mother.

168
00:14:10,985 --> 00:14:13,373
- How many tons have you sold?
- 16 tons.

169
00:14:13,623 --> 00:14:17,401
- Fine. Recover it on the route.
- Okay, ma'am.

170
00:14:19,541 --> 00:14:20,289
- Son.
- Yes.

171
00:14:20,314 --> 00:14:22,547
Do you know how educated
this accountant is?

172
00:14:22,588 --> 00:14:25,588
Mother, he's highly educated.
He even speaks in English.

173
00:14:25,888 --> 00:14:28,798
So why is he bowing down in front of us?

174
00:14:29,079 --> 00:14:32,511
Because educated people respect others.

175
00:14:32,774 --> 00:14:36,253
No. It's because we're really rich.

176
00:14:36,317 --> 00:14:39,717
And your father has earned
this wealth by farming.

177
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:41,337
He achieved this only by studying.

178
00:14:41,362 --> 00:14:45,123
No, son. I'll explain it to you.
Come along.

179
00:14:46,046 --> 00:14:50,118
Yes. -Look, everybody bows to your father.

180
00:14:50,534 --> 00:14:53,021
That man in black coat is a lawyer.

181
00:14:53,195 --> 00:14:55,657
The one in the suit is
the officer-in-charge.

182
00:14:56,052 --> 00:14:57,532
The others too are educated people.

183
00:14:58,038 --> 00:15:00,481
Only education can get you a job.

184
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:03,001
I don't want to be a servant.
I'll be the master.

185
00:15:03,426 --> 00:15:05,493
If you want to become a
master, work in the fields.

186
00:15:05,556 --> 00:15:09,076
Because the real wealth is in the
ground, not in the books.

187
00:15:09,188 --> 00:15:10,435
I'll work in the fields.

188
00:15:11,299 --> 00:15:14,477
Very good.
So what is the need for all this?

189
00:15:14,518 --> 00:15:15,878
Give. I'll throw it.

190
00:15:15,899 --> 00:15:18,339
Not this. Your name is written on this.

191
00:15:18,486 --> 00:15:20,255
If you say so, I'll tear this.

192
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:24,991
[PAPER RUSTLING]

193
00:15:41,792 --> 00:15:42,722
Look, son.

194
00:15:43,129 --> 00:15:46,822
This part of our land is
lying barren for many years.

195
00:15:47,234 --> 00:15:50,392
Forget crops,
not even grass can grow here.

196
00:15:50,759 --> 00:15:55,608
With your hard work,
you've to turn this land into lush fields.

197
00:15:55,665 --> 00:15:56,816
What are you doing?

198
00:15:57,042 --> 00:15:59,561
You're handing a big
task to this small child.

199
00:15:59,799 --> 00:16:02,879
Even strong men couldn't
grow a twig of grass here.

200
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:05,025
How can this child make
this barren land lush?

201
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:41,317
Move.

202
00:16:56,972 --> 00:16:58,033
Mother.

203
00:16:59,429 --> 00:17:00,438
Mother.

204
00:17:02,386 --> 00:17:06,221
Mother. -What are you doing?
Put me down. Leave me.

205
00:17:06,441 --> 00:17:09,329
Are you happy?
Look how lush the fields are.

206
00:17:09,601 --> 00:17:11,260
This was barren land.

207
00:17:11,281 --> 00:17:14,660
I would've even turned a
desert into lush land for you.

208
00:17:14,901 --> 00:17:17,389
How can the son not obey
his mother's command?

209
00:17:28,369 --> 00:17:30,025
Has he put stones in his bag?

210
00:17:31,491 --> 00:17:33,971
- Already you are tired?
- This is the sixth bag.

211
00:17:34,316 --> 00:17:39,299
I feel Ramesh is going for ever. I'm dead.

212
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:41,780
What are you whispering to your wife?

213
00:17:41,819 --> 00:17:43,820
Don't you get time at home?
Have you kept the luggage properly?

214
00:17:43,845 --> 00:17:45,483
- I'm doing it.
- Don't shout at me.

215
00:17:45,524 --> 00:17:46,644
- Am I?
- Yes.

216
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:48,331
Okay.

217
00:17:48,572 --> 00:17:51,772
Shut the trunk properly.
Nothing should be left out.

218
00:17:51,974 --> 00:17:53,987
Got it? Greetings, sister. [FOOT STEPS]

219
00:17:54,013 --> 00:17:56,029
- Ramesh, hurry up. We're getting late.
- Yes, Mother.

220
00:17:57,140 --> 00:17:58,579
- Take care.
- Bye, Uncle.

221
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:02,077
I'll miss you all. Do you miss me?

222
00:18:02,163 --> 00:18:03,940
Goodbye.

223
00:18:09,023 --> 00:18:10,919
Am I a devil?
Why did she scream on seeing me?

224
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,547
If you had been a devil,
she wouldn't have screamed.

225
00:18:12,588 --> 00:18:14,460
But anybody would get
scared of a naked man.

226
00:18:14,501 --> 00:18:16,019
Naked? You've worn your clothes.

227
00:18:16,060 --> 00:18:17,843
- But you've not worn it.
- What are you saying?

228
00:18:18,606 --> 00:18:19,597
Take this towel.

229
00:18:29,761 --> 00:18:31,862
Why are you stopping the car like this?

230
00:18:31,903 --> 00:18:33,903
Move aside. We're getting late.

231
00:18:34,102 --> 00:18:35,752
I'm only making you late.

232
00:18:35,959 --> 00:18:40,222
But you've caused chaos, Laxmi.
You've seized my land.

233
00:18:40,263 --> 00:18:42,078
Which land are you talking about?

234
00:18:42,395 --> 00:18:44,932
It's my land. And it'll remain mine.

235
00:18:44,973 --> 00:18:48,103
You're lying.
That land belongs to my ancestors.

236
00:18:48,352 --> 00:18:50,958
And if you didn't hand
over the land to me...

237
00:18:51,470 --> 00:18:53,847
...I would have to use foul means.

238
00:18:54,346 --> 00:18:57,391
Scoundrel. You threaten me.

239
00:18:57,930 --> 00:18:59,624
Do whatever you want.

240
00:19:00,374 --> 00:19:02,710
I don't argue with filthy men like you.

241
00:19:08,747 --> 00:19:09,823
Let's go, driver.

242
00:19:17,204 --> 00:19:18,910
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

243
00:19:19,612 --> 00:19:21,588
[TRAIN HORN ]

244
00:19:21,766 --> 00:19:24,426
It's time for the train to
depart, but Raju isn't here yet.

245
00:19:24,796 --> 00:19:26,440
Mother. [FOOT STEPS]

246
00:19:27,175 --> 00:19:29,665
- Mother.
- Son, where were you?

247
00:19:29,761 --> 00:19:33,199
I had gone to buy almond
sweets from Chandu's shop.

248
00:19:33,224 --> 00:19:35,794
- So I got late.
- Okay. [TRAIN HORN]

249
00:19:35,858 --> 00:19:37,027
- Come on, Ramesh. Get in the train.
- Okay.

250
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:38,146
The train is leaving.

251
00:19:39,103 --> 00:19:41,263
Stop. Stop. Seek mother's blessings.

252
00:19:41,503 --> 00:19:42,903
- God bless you, son.
- Hurry up. Get in.

